---
source: crates/tirith/tests/help_snapshots.rs
expression: stdout.to_string()
---
Safely download and execute a script

Usage: tirith run [OPTIONS] <URL>

Arguments:
  <URL>  URL to download and execute

Options:
      --no-exec          Download and analyze only, don't execute
      --format <FORMAT>  Output format (default: human) [possible values: human, json]
      --sha256 <SHA256>  Expected SHA-256 hash of the downloaded script (abort if mismatch)
  -h, --help             Print help

Examples:
  tirith run https://get.example-tool.sh
  tirith run --no-exec https://example.com/install.sh
  tirith run --sha256 abc123 https://example.com/install.sh
